Eskom says it has closed unit two on Tuesday as part of general maintenance across its generating fleet. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says it is shutting down one of the units at the Koeberg Power Station for routine maintenance.The power utility says it has closed unit two on Tuesday as part of general maintenance across its generating fleet.Eskom's Khulu Phasiwe said: We are going to shut down this unit for two months and it should be back online soon. It previously used to be three months but we have cut it down to about two months now, this is part of our improvements we have been making on our generating fleet. 